      <templ:var name="name">The Search for The Belat Missan</templ:var>
      <templ:var name="height">700px</templ:var>
    </templ:templ>
  </doc:section>

  <doc:section id="search">
    <doc:title><templ:date/> &mdash; The State of Search</doc:title>
    
    <p>It's a lazy Tuesday afternoon. The air hangs heavy and warm as Alice and Janice debate methods one might employ to accurately guage the airspeed of a sparrow.</p>
    
    <p>Alice is currently dominating with The Matching Windtunnel:</p>
    
    <ol id="windtunnel">
      <li>Build windtunnel</li>
      <li>Get swallow</li>
      <li>Scare swallow</li>
      <li>Release swallow into tunnel</li>
      <li>Increase fan speed until forward motion of swallow stops</li>
      <li>Measure fan speed</li>
    </ol>
    
    <p>To futher research, Alice gets out her laptop and heads to <a href="http://google.com">Google</a>.</p>
    
    <templ:templ name="figure">
      <templ:var name="name">Talking to Google</templ:var>
      <templ:var name="height">250px</templ:var>
    </templ:templ>
    
    <p>She she surfs around for a while huting for "swallow speed," until she finally finds what she's hunting for at <a href="http://style.org/unladenswallow/">13pt</a>.</p>
    
    <templ:templ name="figure">
      <templ:var name="name">Swallowing Speed</templ:var>
      <templ:var name="height">400px</templ:var>
    </templ:templ>
    
    <p>How Alice finally found the information she wanted is known in the parlance of the <acronym title="World Wide Web">web</acronym> as a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/URL"><acronym title="Uniform Resource Locator">URL</acronym></a> (pronounced "earl"). <acronym title="Uniform Resource Locator">URL</acronym>s have three basic parts:</p>
    
